========================
Getting Started: Sensors
========================

This project represents the point we will get to by video 12 in a Getting STARTed series.  
In this video series, we'll be building a project using the analog light and digital I2C temperature sensors on the Atmel IO1 Xplained Pro extension board.

- Learn how to use the data visualizer to test each development step

- Use some of the latest Atmel Studio 7 features through the course of this development

`Getting Started Sensors <https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLtQdQmNK_0DS3K9jIyPPMc9m6Tjobtj3d>`_

Two hands-on labs help you to apply your newly acquired knowledge:


`SAM Training: Start and Low Power <http://microchipdeveloper.com/32arm:m0-saml-training>`_

**Lab1:**
  * Use the Atmel Start Web UI to generate a Studio IDE project and source code based on the the Atmel Software Framework (ASF).
  * Create Atmel Start project
  * Add USART driver for debug messages
  * Add ADC and I2C driver for temperature and light sensor
  * Add SPI driver to display temp and light sensor data using Atmel Data Visualizer

**Lab2:**
  *  Place the SAM L21 into its five power modes and use Studio IDE's Data Visualizer to measure the power consumption.
  *  Create Atmel Start project
  *  Configure the oscillators and clocks
  *  Configure the External Interrupt Controller
  *  Configure SW0 push button using Atmel Start PINMUX Configurator
  *  Place the SAM L21 into its 5 power modes and measure the power consumption using Atmel Data Visualizer

=========================
Supported Evaluation Kits
=========================

* ATSAML21-XPRO-B 
* ATSAMD21-XPRO 
* ATSAMW25-XPRO

============
Sensor board
============

* I/O1 Xplained Pro

==========
Middleware
==========

* Temperature Sensor

=======
Drivers
=======

* USART
* I2C
* SPI
* Delay
* ADC

==================
Interface settings
==================

* Connect I/O1 Xplained Pro to SAML21-XPRO-B -> **EXT1**
* Connect I/O1 Xplained Pro to SAMD21-XPRO -> **EXT1**
* Connect I/O1 Xplained Pro to SAMW25-XPRO -> **EXT1**

* AT30TSE75X Temperature Sensor
    * 11-bits resolution

* USART
    * No parity
    * 8-bits character size
    * 1 stop bit
    * 115200 baud-rate
    * No Hardware Handshake

* I2C Master
    * 400000 baud-rate

* SPI
    * 50000 baud-rate
    * 8-bits character size

* ADC
    * 8-bits resolution
    * Internal bandgap reference

================
Running the demo
================

1. Press Download Pack and save the .atzip file
2. Import .atzip file into Atmel Studio 7, File->Import->Atmel Start Project.
3. Build and flash into supported evaluation board
4. Open Data Visualizer in Atmel Studio
5. Configure Serial Port, Data Stream protocol and Graph, you should see the temperature and light sensors data


==================================
Data Streamer Protocol Config file
==================================

Following is the config file settings for Data Streamer portocol in Data Visualizer

 B,1,1,Temperature
 
 D,1,2,Light
